# Prime Fibernet — Project Context

## Migration

Flutter → React Native (Expo SDK 50, TypeScript 5, strict mode).
Read the Flutter source for *intent*, not structure — see `flutter-migration.mdc`
for translation patterns. Never port Flutter widget trees 1:1.

## Architecture

Single Expo app serving three roles from one codebase: Customer, Officer, Admin.

- Role is resolved once at login from `profiles.role` and drives navigation,
  not just UI visibility — a screen a role shouldn't see should not be
  reachable, not just hidden behind a conditional render.
- Never assume which role is active. Check `useAuth().role` explicitly in
  any new screen/component that touches role-specific data.

## Backend & State

- Supabase: Postgres + Auth + Realtime + Storage + Edge Functions
- All schema changes go through Supabase MCP — never hand-edit prod tables
  outside of a migration file checked into the repo
- State: Redux Toolkit + RTK Query for ALL server state. No component-level
  useState holding server data, no parallel fetch logic outside RTK Query slices
- Local/UI-only state (modals, sheet visibility, form drafts) can use
  component state or a dedicated UI slice — never mix with API slices

## Stack versions (verify before using any API)

RN 0.73+, TypeScript 5 (strict), Zod, NativeWind, React Navigation 6,
React Hook Form. If unsure whether a stack API exists at this version,
check node_modules or the lockfile before using it — do not assume from
training data. See `stack-docs.mdc`.

## Folder layout (do not deviate without asking)

- Screens: `apps/unified-app/src/screens/<role>/<feature>/`
- Components: `apps/unified-app/src/components/{shared,admin,officer,customer}/`
- Store: `apps/unified-app/src/store/{slices,api}/`
- Types: `apps/unified-app/src/types/`
- Hooks: `apps/unified-app/src/hooks/`
- Utils: `apps/unified-app/src/utils/`

## Definition of done for any feature in this codebase

A feature is not complete until it has:

1. Loading, error, and empty states (no exceptions — see `unified-app-standards.mdc`)
2. RLS policy reviewed/written if it touches a new table or new access pattern
3. Role-gated correctly (see Architecture above)
4. No console.log left in — use the existing logger if one exists, otherwise ask

If any of these is skipped, say so explicitly rather than presenting it as done.
